headline: Bitcoin, Ethereum Fall With No Crypto Rally in Sight. Coinbase, Strategy Stocks Suffer.
summary: Bitcoin and other cryptocurrencies were lower on Tuesday amid a period of stagnant trading for digital assets, which have given back major gains in recent months.  The price of Bitcoin fell 2.5% over the past 24 hours to $87,700.  The largest digital asset hit a record high above $125,000 in October but has since retreated dramatically.
